(ooc: hotmail didn't send my post again, but it was where Element was hit by 
a shot and then fired more missiles at Abominus. I'll continue from there)

(and JP, that was so cheap!! Cyndro is blocking all enemy transmissions, so 
your bots cant communicate!!!! i better not see you send another 
transmission)


Element turned, seeing Hell Beast and his troops enter the battle. He 
growled. Looking back at Abominus, he saw that Galaxor had engaged him in 
combat by now, and attacking an already fighting bot was pointless. He 
turned toward the eastern bots and charged at them. Four missiles flew out 
of his two missile launchers and Element mentally guided one toward each of 
the bots he was attacking (Aquarious, Black Aracnia, Bezerker, and 
Quickstrike).


Cyndro almost laughed as some morons positioned themselves between the CF 
and the Element (Hell Beast, Tankkor, Rampage, and Inferno). That was the 
most stupid thing he had ever seen. Arming all his weapons (the ship's 
weapons :), he fired them all at this group of four dumb preds. Two 
missiles, four EMP blasts, and four laser shots were fired at each bot. The 
round disk thingy on top of the Element, which was still jamming all enemy 
transmissions, flashed and sent a shockwave at the four bots, strong enough 
to throw them off their feet and leave them defenceless against the oncoming 
weaponfire. The missiles were homing missiles, and the EMP blasts and 
laserfire were very well aimed.




A portal opened above earth and a fairly large ship with Maximal markings 
emerged from it, followed by heavy weaponfire. Behind it, a Predacon ship 
emerged. The two ships raced toward earth, though at every shot, Predacon 
weaponfire was getting closer and closer to hitting the Maximal ship. 
Finally, the Maximal ship returned fire, hitting the Predacon ship straight 
on, but not before being hit in the engines with a Predacon shot.

The Predacon vessel exploded since the shot had gone through crucial parts 
of the ship, but the Maximal vessel angled toward earth and kept flying. 
Inside, the crew scrambled to their escape pods.
